	<body>
		<category name="Class Mods Redux">
			<category name="Description">
				<comment>By Aaron0000</comment>
				<comment>Modifies a large number of class mods to be more balanced, fitting, specialized, or otherwise interesting. Also enables all purple class mods to have a small chance of spawning as a Legendary version, if it is level 50 or higher.</comment>
				<comment>NOTE;</comment>
				<comment>Due to how I rigged the prefixes and names, it is likely you will see incomplete names displayed below the EXP bar and underneath a partner's hud. This isn't fixable.</comment>
				<comment>Given how ALL purple coms have a chance to spawn as Legendary now, there are a few that would essentially be duplicates of the already existing Legendary coms. The standard Legendary COMs (other than the Terramorphous COMs) have had "Genuine" added to their title to distinguish them. The modded ones also tend to be slightly worse than the genuine ones.</comment>
				<comment>If using my Allegiance COMs, load them after this mod to have the Allegiance COMs overwrite most Tiny Tina COMs other than Chaotic Evil.</comment>
				<comment>Any mod that adds individual skins to the Tina class mods will override the skin changes of the Legendary specialization part. Either disable those skin changes to allow Legendary recoloring on Tina COMs, or don't.</comment>
				<comment>If using the BLassic mod (Borderlands Classic), load this mod after BLassic and activate the "BLassic fixes" at the bottom of the file.</comment>
				<comment>Credit and thanks to Sir Umnei for his UI stuff.</comment>
				<category name="Class Mod Changes">
					<comment>Below are the changes given to each class mod. The first three skills are what can typically be found on it, while any skills in parenthesis are found only on the Legendary variant.</comment>
					<comment>Any class mods not listed below are unchanged, consisting of a few of the standard Legendary coms in the game.</comment>
					<comment>If a class mod replaces skills, I have given the variant of that class mod a new prefix to match it. Said prefixes are listed at the end of each of the upcoming, respective lines.</comment>
					<comment>Any class mods that boost Inconcievable or Close Enough is capped at +4. You can only reach a maximum of 90% chance to not consume ammo or ricochet towards an enemy.</comment>
					<comment>Any class mods that boosts Nth Degree are capped at +3, so that only up to every 2nd bullet will ricochet towards an enemy.</comment>
					<category name="Changes">
						<category name="Salvador">
							<comment>Beast - Boosts Explosive Damage, Reload Speed, Ain't Got Time to Bleed, Incite, Sexual Tyrannosaurus, (Out of Bubblegum, and All in the Reflexes.) Savagge prefix is now Brazen. </comment>
							<comment>Berserker - Boosts Cooldown rate, Lay Waste, Last Longer, Yippee-Ki-Yay, (Bus That Can't Slow Down, and Divergent Likeness.)</comment>
							<comment>Devastator - Boosts Team Magazine Size, Quick Draw, Just Got Real, Divergent Likeness, (Filled to the Brim, and Inconcievable.) Hoarding prefix is now Perpetual.</comment>
							<comment>Hoarder - Boosts the same things as the normal Legendary Hoarder when it spawns as a Legendary.</comment>
							<comment>Monk - Boosts Money Shot, Asbestos, All in the Reflexes, (Ain't Got TIme to Bleed, and Last Longer.)</comment>
							<comment>Raider - Boosts movement speed, lowers shield capacity, boosts Bus That Can't Slow Down, Money Shot, Incite, (Out of Bubblegum, and Yippee-Ki-Yay.) Cocky prefix is now Nitro.</comment>
							<comment>Renegade - Boosts Pistol Gun Damage, lowers Pistol Accuracy, boosts I'm Your Huckleberry, Incite, Divergent Likeness, (Quick Draw, and Lay Waste.) Vengeful prefix replaced with Wild, Cocky prefix replaced with Pragmatic.  </comment>
							<comment>Tank - Boosts shield capacity and recharge rate, I'm the Juggernaut, Hard to Kill, Asbestos, (Incite, and Bus That Can't Slow Down.) </comment>
							<comment>Titan - Boosts Health regen, Gun Damage, lowers Shield Capacity, boosts Hard to Kill, Sexual Tyrannosaurus, Ain't Got Time to Bleed, (Out of Bubblegum, and Asbestos.) Grand prefix replaced with Hulking, Grand prefix replaced with Altered. </comment>
							<comment>War Dog - Boosts Reload Speed, Magazine Size, 5 Shots or 6, Out of BUbblegum, Lay Waste, (Locked and Loaded, and Inconcievable.) Hoarding prefix replaced with Rabid.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Berserker - Boosts Melee Override Cooldown, Action Skill Cooldown Time, Melee Damage, Incite, Keep It Piping Hot, All In The Reflexes, Yippe Ki Yay, I'm the Juggarnaut, and Asbestos.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Titan - Boosts Health regen, Gun Damage, lowers Shield Capacity, boosts Hard to Kill, Sexual Tyrannosaurus, Ain't Got Time to Bleed, Out of Bubblegum, and Asbestos. Grand prefix replaced with Hulking, Grand prefix replaced with Altered. </comment>

					<category name="Rationale">
						<category name="Salvador">
							<comment>Beast - Just Got Real just kinda sucks, so I gave it a marginally more useful skill. Explosive damage is because 1. More useful than health capacity on a Gunzerker and 2. Torgue.</comment>
							<comment>Berserker - Concentrates on maximizing Gunzerking, so Bus and Divergent were added on the Legendary variant to augment that.</comment>
							<comment>Devastator - Inconcievable is awesome, and I wanted to open up some more options for useful Gunzerker COMs.</comment>
							<comment>Monk - Monk's already great, but Sexy T-Rex was a bit too far down the skill tree, hence Reflexes. Time to Bleed and Last Longer aid with raid bosses.</comment>
							<comment>Raider - The Monk COM is essentially the bread-and-butter raiding COM for Salvador, so I figured I'd make the Raider the mobbing/Banshee equivalent.</comment>
							<comment>Renegade - Now more effective as a Pistol-themed COM. </comment>
							<comment>Titan - Wanted to make it more distinct from the Tank. Titan now heavily focuses on health and regeneration.</comment>
							<comment>Tank - Now focuses on shields and resisting things. The Legendary variant gets Incite and Bus because everything else was basically already covered by the Titan COM.</comment>
							<comment>War Dog - Seemed to focus on holding and putting out as many bullets as possible, so Lay Waste (and Locked & Loaded and Inconcievable) are there to stress that further.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Berserker - As it was before, it was doing a half-assed attempt of emulating Brick. I made it a full-blown Melee COM.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Axton">
							<comment>Engineer - Simply mimics the genuine Legendary Engineer COM, only becaue I needed something since all Purple COMs can spawn as Legendary now.</comment>
							<comment>Grenadier - Battlefront fits the Explosive COM better than Impact does. On the Legendary version, Duty Calls also boosts Explosive damage in some cases.</comment>
							<comment>Gunner - Gunner COM wants to throw out as many bullets as possible, so Ready and Ranger aid in that a little more on the Legendary version.</comment>
							<comment>Pointman - Simply mimics the genuine Legendary Pointman COM, only becaue I needed something since all Purple COMs can spawn as Legendary now.</comment>
							<comment>Ranger - Steady and Expertise add some extra all-around boosts on the Legendary version.</comment>
							<comment>Rifleman - Assault Rifles eat up a lot of bullets, so Ammo Regen helps fill the ammo belly back up. Overload and Steady help put out more bullets on the Legendary variant. </comment>
							<comment>Shock Trooper - With boosted kill-skill duration, it can now can better realize itself as a Kill Skill COM.</comment>
							<comment>Specialist - Simply expands on the UCP's Shotgun-themed COM.</comment>
							<comment>Tactician - It already boosted Team Shield Recharge Rate and Team Shield Recharge Delay, so I figured it may as well go full Shield-COM. Should be quite the shield tank.</comment>
							<comment>Veteran - Rather than having a situational skill like Last Ditch Effort, Ready is always active. Also, Tediore-chuckers will appreciate this along with Overload and Battlefront.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Zer0">
							<comment>Infiltrator - It's trying to be a Gun/Melee Hybrid COM, and thus I gave it more useful skills for said purpose.</comment>
							<comment>Killer - Simply mimics the genuine Legendary Killer COM, only becaue I needed something since all Purple COMs can spawn as Legendary now.</comment>
							<comment>Ninja - Resurgence is largely invalidated by Moxxi-weapon melee or the Law/Order combo. Gave it something more useful.</comment>
							<comment>Professional - The stat boosts for it are Shield Capacity and Reload speed, so I gave it skills to accentuate that.</comment>
							<comment>Rogue - Like the Wind is (before 3.0 patch) not very useful, as well as placed rather deep into the Bloodshed tree. I replaced it with a skill that is more likely to be picked up by any Zer0 player, not just Melee builds.</comment>
							<comment>#Shot - Might as well give the niche Infinity build a bone. Also because two out of three skills had #Shot in the title.</comment>
							<comment>Sniper - Killer's simply more useful than Precisi0n in most scenarios, and the ammo regen helps in between fights.</comment>
							<comment>Spy - Spy focuses on being in and utilizing Deception as much as possible, and the skills present on it help achieve that.</comment>
							<comment>Stalker - C0unterstrike has nothing to do with pistols. Innervate has a bit more use with pistols in comparison.</comment>
							<comment>Survivor - Fearless is for when shields are down, and Grim is to help shields get back up. Gives a little punch without having to rely on Rising Sh0t (which is now more prominent in the #Shot COM). Glass Tank builds may appreciate this.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Sniper - Applied normal Sniper COM changes to match up with it.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Ninja - Same with the normal Ninja COM, Resurgence is null in the face of Moxxi.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Maya">
							<comment>Banshee - Banshee's largely only used for Fleet shenanigans, so I decided to make it more speed themed and moved the flamey bits to the Fox COM, hence fire rate and reload buffs.</comment>
							<comment>Binder - Wreck fits a Phaselock-themed COM more than Reaper, and Elated/Chain Reaction further accent that on the Legendary version.</comment>
							<comment>Cat - The SMG damage was off by a decimal point in the code, and it felt odd for one specific-weapon-themed COM in particular to be as much as three times stronger than some other COMs.</comment>
							<comment>Cleric - Restoration is largely unnecessary to invest more than one point into. Foresight is a reasonably more useful skill to invest into, and Wreck/Ward (when Legendary) contribute to a general purpose COM.</comment>
							<comment>Fox - Fox needed some firepower, so now Immolate and Backdraft are there. Incendiary damage boost is there to further up the firepower, and Helios/Blight Phoenix maximize the heat when it becomes Legendary.</comment>
							<comment>Matriarch - Was treading on Nurse territory, so I gave it Reaper for it to function as a more offensively-inclined health com.</comment>
							<comment>Trickster - The only theme the Trickster COM seemed to have going for it is ricochets, but Maya lacks anything else in that department so Foresight and Wreck exist on the Legendary version to bolster that further.</comment>
							<comment>Warder - Between Shield Capacity and Ward, it was trying to be a Shield-focused COM. Inertia serves to accentuate that further, in a manner more useful than Recompense.</comment>
							<comment>Witch - Leave fire to the Fox COM, this one is a bit more Corrosive focused. Suspension is more useful and fits in with the theme of witchcraft.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Nurse - Legendary Nurse isn't running short of ways to regenerate health passively. Life Tap gives it a more active option.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Binder - Same as the normal version, Wreck fits Phaselock themed COMs more.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Cat - Same as normal Cat, SMG damage adjusted.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Gaige">
							<comment>Anarchist - Fancy Mathematics and Annoyed Android did not really have a lot to do with the theme of Anarchy. And Death from Above is mediocre.</comment>
							<comment>Catalyst - Zapper and Catalyst were vying for the same role. Catalyst is now more focused on causing DoTs and strengthening them.</comment>
							<comment>Jill of All Trades - The COM itself has ok skills, as it is trying to be a general purpose COM. Just that the stat boosts were baffling, so they were made into general boosts.</comment>
							<comment>Necromancer - Was oddly focused on boosting Deathtrap more than it boosted you. Now it boosts nice stuff from each tree, more fitting of a fit-to-your-needs COM.</comment>
							<comment>Prodigy - A lot of Gaige's COMs seem to gravitate towards being some variation of a general-pupose COM. Prodigy is a bit more accuracy/reload focused, or as much as Gaige's skills will let it be.</comment>
							<comment>Punk - Focuses on Fire Rate and Lowered Mag Size as much as the skills will allow, and the rest of the skills generalize it.</comment>
							<comment>Roboteer - Traded bulk for more speed, as well as more frequent use of Deathtrap.</comment>
							<comment>Sweetheart - It was halfway to being a health-themed COM, so now it goes further in that direction. That, and Gaige could use a COM for glass cannon builds.</comment>
							<comment>Technophile - It seemed to be trying to be a shield com before. Strength of Five Gorillas and Interspursed Outburst didn't really have much to do with shields. The skills it has now have quite a lot to do with shields.</comment>
							<comment>Zapper - As mentioned before, Zapper and Catalyst were competing for the same role. Zapper is now the more direct option for electric-themed builds.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Mechromancer - It was already fairly similar to the Legendary Roboteer, so the skills were changed to differentiate it.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Anarchist - Because it makes sense for the LEGENDARY ANARCHIST to boost how many stacks you can have.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Catalyst - Same as the normal Zapper/Catalyst relationship, focuses slightly more on DoTs compared to the Zapper.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Krieg">
							<comment>Barbarian - Before, it seemed like it was trying to do a little bit of everything. Now, with Blood-Filled Guns boosting magazine size, Embrace the Pain boosting fire rate, and Fire Fiend boosting accuracy and reload speed, combined with the stat possibilities of the Tina COMs, it is now a more versatile (and useful) COM.</comment>
							<comment>Blister - Legendary version further expands on the Bloodlust-qualities of the standard.</comment>
							<comment>Crunch - Other than Strip the Flesh, the other skills weren't really contributing to an Explosive-build much. Now it has more useful skills to work with (and Tediore-builds will appreciate the Blood-Filled Guns boost).</comment>
							<comment>Meat - Meat and Slab were competing with each other for the role of health COM. So I turned the Meat COM into a Shotgun-themed COM. Krieg needed a good shotgun COM given how close and personal he tends to be.</comment>
							<comment>Reaper - Reaper - Mania/Hellborn builds will be able to relaibly set things on fire during a Buzz Axe Rampage, as well as use Blood Overdrive effectively when not Rampaging.</comment>
							<comment>Sickle - No actual changes other than making it "Legendary-able", and even then it just mimics the actual Legendary Sickle COM.</comment>
							<comment>Slab - Meat and Slab were competing with each other for the role of health COM. So I made the Slab the definitive health COM. Fuel the Rampage is largely useless after getting Release the Beast, so I replaced it with a more useful skill for early game.</comment>
							<comment>Toast - Where Torch dabbles more in DoTs, Toast focuses more on directly melting enemies with your bullets.</comment>
							<comment>Torch - Torch seemed to focus on applying, maintaining, and empowering DoTs before. Now it is a longer-lasting Torch due to the reduced burn damage on the user when equipped.</comment>
							<comment>Wound - Skills are no longer all over the place, now they are focused on putting out as many bullets as possible within a short time.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Psycho - It was trying to be a big, general purpose COM without actually accomplishing much. Now it can actually accomplish things, while most of the skills also have synergy with other skill trees.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Reaper - Completely unchanged. The non-Genuine version of the Legendary Reaper, though is more focused on melee/fire hybrid action.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Sickle - Salt the Wound and Pain is Power apply similar benefits, but Salt the Wound is both far more potent and not reliant on Hellborn.</comment>
							<comment>Legendary Torch - Legendary Torch does not have much difficulty creating and maintaining flames, so it has been replaced with a more useful skill while still leaving the Toast COM as an option for more raw power. Also added the normal Torch COM burn resistance.</comment>
						</category>
					</category>
				</category>
			</category>
			<category name="Code">
				<category name="Sir Umnei's UI Fix (Required)">
					<code profiles="default">set GD_ClassMods.Title.Title_ClassMod PartName COM</code>
					<category name="Enable All DLC Skills on Any Class Mod">
